7 A Concurrent Resolution celebrating April 27, 2025,
as the 90th anniversary of the establishment of the
8 USDA Soil Conservation Service; and commending the
past and present employees of the Service for their
9 work.
10
11
12 WHEREAS, the Dust Bowl of the 1930s was the worst environmental
13 disaster of the 20th century in our nation, and it had a profound
14 impact on the people and the land of Oklahoma; and
15 WHEREAS, the Dust Bowl served as the catalyst for the nation and
16 for Oklahoma to commit to protecting our soil resources through a
17 soil conservation program; and
18 WHEREAS, the United States Department of Agriculture Soil
19 Conservation Service (now the Natural Resources Conservation
20 Service) was established on April 27, 1935, to assist farmers,
21 ranchers, and other landowners in protecting soil and water
22 resources on private lands; and
23 WHEREAS, the Natural Resources Conservation Service for the past
24 90 years has provided a vital public service by supplying technical
