1 expe rtise and financial assistance to private landowners for the
2 conservation of soil and water resources; and
3 WHEREAS, the Natural Resources Conservation Service has
4 effectively partnered with Oklahoma's conservation districts and the
5 Oklahoma Conservation Commission to conserve and protect the state's
6 soil and water resources; and
7 WHEREAS, the work of the Natural Resources Conservation Service
8 has been a great benefit to the state and continues to be an
9 important resource for landowners who are working to be good
10 stewards of their land.
11 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
12 OF THE 1ST SESSION OF THE 60TH OKLAHOMA LEGISLATURE, THE SENATE
13 CONCURRING THEREIN:
14 THAT the Oklahoma House of Representatives and Oklahoma State
15 Senate do hereby celebrate April 27, 2025, as the 90th anniversary
16 of the establishment of the USDA Soil Conservation Service (now the
17 Natural Resources Conservation Service) and commends the past and
18 present employees of the Service for their work in conserving the
19 soil and water resources of our state.
